<h1>grigson</h1>
<p class="intro">A markup language for chord charts, with a parser and system of renderers that output
to HTML, plain text, and other formats. Transpose to any key, switch between light and
dark themes, choose a typeface, and customise notation to taste.</p>

<section class="feature">
  <h2>The .chart format</h2>
  <p>Charts are plain-text files with YAML front matter and pipe-delimited bars. They're readable
  without any tooling — open one in any text editor and the structure is immediately clear.</p>
  <p><a href="{{ '/language/' | url }}">Learn the language →</a></p>
  {% highlight "grigson" %}---
title: "Blue Bossa"
key: C minor
meter: 4/4
---

| Cm7 | Cm7 | Fm7 | Fm7 |
| Dm7b5 | G7 | Cm | % |
| Ebm7 | Ab7 | Dbmaj7 | % |
| Dm7b5 | G7 | Cm | % ||.{% endhighlight %}
</section>

<section class="feature">
  <h2>Rendered output</h2>
  <p>Drop <code>&lt;grigson-chart&gt;</code> into any page and the chart renders to HTML —
  no build step required for the browser.</p>
  <p><a href="{{ '/usage/html-renderer/' | url }}">HTML renderer docs →</a></p>
  <grigson-chart normalise>
    <template>---
title: "Blue Bossa"
key: C minor
meter: 4/4
---

| Cm7 | Cm7 | Fm7 | Fm7 |
| Dm7b5 | G7 | Cm | % |
| Ebm7 | Ab7 | Dbmaj7 | % |
| Dm7b5 | G7 | Cm | % ||.</template>
  </grigson-chart>
</section>

<section class="feature">
  <h2>Transposition</h2>
  <p>Charts transpose to any key on the fly. Useful for instruments in B♭ or E♭,
  or for practicing in all twelve keys.</p>
  <p><a href="{{ '/usage/custom-elements/' | url }}">Custom elements docs →</a></p>
  <div class="demo-controls">
    <label for="transpose-key-select">Key:</label>
    <select id="transpose-key-select">
      <option value="">C minor (original)</option>
      <option value="C#">C♯ minor</option>
      <option value="D">D minor</option>
      <option value="Eb">E♭ minor</option>
      <option value="E">E minor</option>
      <option value="F">F minor</option>
      <option value="F#">F♯ minor</option>
      <option value="G">G minor</option>
      <option value="G#">G♯ minor</option>
      <option value="A">A minor</option>
      <option value="Bb">B♭ minor</option>
      <option value="B">B minor</option>
    </select>
  </div>
  <grigson-chart id="transpose-demo" normalise>
    <template>---
title: "Blue Bossa"
key: C minor
meter: 4/4
---

| Cm7 | Cm7 | Fm7 | Fm7 |
| Dm7b5 | G7 | Cm | % |
| Ebm7 | Ab7 | Dbmaj7 | % |
| Dm7b5 | G7 | Cm | % ||.</template>
  </grigson-chart>
  <script>
    document.getElementById('transpose-key-select').addEventListener('change', function(e) {
      var chart = document.getElementById('transpose-demo');
      if (e.target.value) chart.setAttribute('transpose-key', e.target.value);
      else chart.removeAttribute('transpose-key');
    });
  </script>
</section>

<section class="feature">
  <h2>Light and dark themes</h2>
  <p>Built-in CSS custom properties make it easy to match any colour scheme.
  The slider below compares the two built-in themes side by side.</p>
  <p><a href="{{ '/customize/css/' | url }}">CSS custom properties →</a></p>
  <div class="theme-demo-stage" id="theme-demo-stage"
       role="slider" tabindex="0"
       aria-label="Theme comparison: drag to reveal light or dark mode"
       aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100" aria-valuenow="50">
    <grigson-chart normalise id="theme-demo-chart">
      <style>
        :host {
          position: relative;
          overflow: hidden;
        }
        .chart-light {
          box-sizing: border-box;
          background: #ffffff;
          color: #1a1a1a;
          padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
        }
        .chart-dark {
          box-sizing: border-box;
          position: absolute;
          inset: 0;
          background: #1e1e1e;
          color: #d4d4d4;
          padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
          clip-path: inset(0 calc(100% - var(--split, 50%)) 0 0);
        }
      </style>
      <grigson-html-renderer class="chart-light"></grigson-html-renderer>
      <grigson-html-renderer class="chart-dark"></grigson-html-renderer>
      <template>---
title: "Blue Bossa"
key: C minor
meter: 4/4
---

| Cm7 | Cm7 | Fm7 | Fm7 |
| Dm7b5 | G7 | Cm | % |
| Ebm7 | Ab7 | Dbmaj7 | % |
| Dm7b5 | G7 | Cm | % ||.</template>
    </grigson-chart>
    <div class="theme-demo-divider" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="theme-demo-handle">◀▶</div>
    </div>
    <span class="theme-demo-tag theme-demo-tag--dark" aria-hidden="true">Dark</span>
    <span class="theme-demo-tag theme-demo-tag--light" aria-hidden="true">Light</span>
  </div>
  <script>
    (function () {
      var stage = document.getElementById('theme-demo-stage');
      var prefersDark = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;
      var split = prefersDark ? 70 : 30;

      function setSplit(value) {
        split = Math.max(0, Math.min(100, value));
        stage.style.setProperty('--split', split + '%');
        stage.setAttribute('aria-valuenow', Math.round(split));
      }

      setSplit(split);

      stage.addEventListener('pointerdown', function (e) {
        stage.setPointerCapture(e.pointerId);
        var rect = stage.getBoundingClientRect();
        setSplit(((e.clientX - rect.left) / rect.width) * 100);
      });

      stage.addEventListener('pointermove', function (e) {
        if (!stage.hasPointerCapture(e.pointerId)) return;
        var rect = stage.getBoundingClientRect();
        setSplit(((e.clientX - rect.left) / rect.width) * 100);
      });

      stage.addEventListener('keydown', function (e) {
        if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft' || e.key === 'ArrowDown') setSplit(split - 5);
        else if (e.key === 'ArrowRight' || e.key === 'ArrowUp') setSplit(split + 5);
      });
    }());
  </script>
</section>

<section class="feature">
  <h2>Chord symbols</h2>
  <p>Two notation presets ship out of the box — the default symbolic style (♭ ♯ △ ø) and
  the Real Book style (MI, MA, MI7(♭5)). You can also define your own preset with any HTML fragments.</p>
  <p><a href="{{ '/customize/notation/' | url }}">Notation presets →</a></p>
  <div class="demo-controls">
    <button id="notation-btn-symbolic" class="active" onclick="setNotation('')">Symbolic</button>
    <button id="notation-btn-realbook" onclick="setNotation('realbook')">Real Book</button>
  </div>
  <grigson-chart id="notation-demo" normalise>
    <grigson-html-renderer id="notation-renderer"></grigson-html-renderer>
    <template>---
title: "Blue Bossa"
key: C minor
meter: 4/4
---

| Cm7 | Cm7 | Fm7 | Fm7 |
| Dm7b5 | G7 | Cm | % |
| Ebm7 | Ab7 | Dbmaj7 | % |
| Dm7b5 | G7 | Cm | % ||.</template>
  </grigson-chart>
  <script>
    function setNotation(preset) {
      var renderer = document.getElementById('notation-renderer');
      if (preset) renderer.setAttribute('notation-preset', preset);
      else renderer.removeAttribute('notation-preset');
      document.getElementById('notation-btn-symbolic').classList.toggle('active', preset === '');
      document.getElementById('notation-btn-realbook').classList.toggle('active', preset === 'realbook');
    }
  </script>
</section>

<section class="feature">
  <h2>Typefaces</h2>
  <p>Choose from three built-in typeface styles — or supply your own font via a CSS custom property.</p>
  <p><a href="{{ '/customize/typefaces/' | url }}">Typefaces docs →</a></p>
  <div class="demo-controls">
    <button id="typeface-btn-sans" class="active" onclick="setTypeface('')">Sans</button>
    <button id="typeface-btn-serif" onclick="setTypeface('serif')">Serif</button>
    <button id="typeface-btn-cursive" onclick="setTypeface('cursive')">Cursive</button>
  </div>
  <grigson-chart id="typeface-demo" normalise>
    <grigson-html-renderer id="typeface-renderer"></grigson-html-renderer>
    <template>---
title: "Blue Bossa"
key: C minor
meter: 4/4
---

| Cm7 | Cm7 | Fm7 | Fm7 |
| Dm7b5 | G7 | Cm | % |
| Ebm7 | Ab7 | Dbmaj7 | % |
| Dm7b5 | G7 | Cm | % ||.</template>
  </grigson-chart>
  <script>
    function setTypeface(value) {
      var renderer = document.getElementById('typeface-renderer');
      if (value) renderer.setAttribute('typeface', value);
      else renderer.removeAttribute('typeface');
      document.getElementById('typeface-btn-sans').classList.toggle('active', value === '');
      document.getElementById('typeface-btn-serif').classList.toggle('active', value === 'serif');
      document.getElementById('typeface-btn-cursive').classList.toggle('active', value === 'cursive');
    }
  </script>
</section>
